{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The review input is scoped to changed lines only (not full modified files).","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure is usually at local module handoff (diff parser -> hunk/line filter -> review-input builder). A unit test of one helper can pass while wiring still leaks unchanged lines.","test_description":"Run an integration test with a fixture PR diff containing large unchanged regions plus small changed hunks across multiple files. Execute the real scoping pipeline and assert the produced review payload includes only changed-line snippets/hunks and excludes unchanged file content.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Inline comments are attached to correct diff positions on the PR.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"GitHub diff-position semantics are external and easy to get wrong (position vs line, renames, multi-hunk files). In-process mocks often hide real API validation/placement failures.","test_description":"Against a real test PR on GitHub, post inline comments using the production mapping logic for several target lines (single hunk, multi-hunk, edge hunk). Fetch posted review comments via API and verify each comment is anchored to the intended file and diff location in the PR.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.75,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The agent finds at least one real defect in a PR containing a known introduced bug.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on real model judgment (defect detection quality), not just deterministic wiring. Mocked/model-stubbed tests cannot validate this failure mode.","test_description":"Use a benchmark PR fixture with a seeded known bug and realistic surrounding code.